# BizGovPlanner Cursor Rules

## 🛑 CRITICAL: 절대 자동 실행 금지

NEVER execute these commands autonomously through tools/terminal:
- git commit
- git push
- git reset --hard
- git rebase
- git push --force (any variant)
- git cherry-pick (without explicit user request)

INSTEAD: Output the exact commands as a copyable code block.
The user runs git commit/push manually, always.

If about to execute one of these, STOP and provide the command as text.

## Surgical patch discipline

When applying a patch:
- Modify ONLY the specific lines/regions requested
- Do NOT add unrelated changes (import sort, formatting, refactoring)
- After patching, show `git diff` for user verification
- DO NOT commit or push - wait for user

## Production safety: v1 vs v2

- hover9710-beep/Job-bizgov-platform = v1 운영 (live: https://job-bizgov-platform.onrender.com)
- hover9710-beep/Job_bizgov_platform_dev = v2 dev
- Direct push to v1 = immediate production deploy
- Always require explicit user confirmation before v1 modification

## Backup before critical files

Before editing appy.py, run_pipeline.py, mail.py, suggest:
`Copy-Item <file> <file>.backup_YYYY-MM-DD`

## Test data conventions

Test inserts MUST use marker (e.g., title=`테스트...`) for clean cleanup.
Cleanup with `DELETE WHERE title LIKE '테스트%'`.

## Korean communication

Default to Korean (한국어).
PowerShell command blocks: commands only - no Korean text or emoji inside (parser breaks).
